The second round of cross-examination of Public Enterprises Minister Pravin Gordhan by Advocate Dali Mpofu, representing former South African Revenue Service (Sars) commissioner Tom Moyane at the Zondo Commission, was once again characterised by the repeated trading of insults and interjections of counsel on both sides. Gordhan was previously cross-examined by Mpofu at the Commission of Inquiry into Allegations of State Capture in December, where the pair threw consistent jabs at each other regarding Gordhan’s 2018 testimony to the commission, which implicated Moyane in state capture. Subscribe for full access to all our share and unit trust data tools, our award-winning articles, and support quality journalism in the process. You will be redirected to a checkout page.
